## 5. Input Validation (MANDATORY)

### 5.1 Validation Layers

**Two layers of validation:**

1. **Schema-level validation** (GraphQL type system):
   - Non-null checks (`!`)
   - Type checks (String, Int, DateTime)
   - Enum validation

2. **Business-level validation** (resolver/service layer):
   - Format validation (email, phone, URL)
   - Range validation (min/max length, min/max value)
   - Business rules (start time < end time, unique email, etc.)

**Pattern:**

```java
// Resolver layer (Spring GraphQL)
@MutationMapping
public CreateEventPayload createEvent(@Valid @Argument CreateEventInput input) {
    // Spring validation runs automatically due to @Valid
    // If validation fails, GraphQL error is returned

    // Business validation in service layer
    return eventService.createEvent(input);
}

// Input DTO (Java)
public record CreateEventInput(
    @NotBlank(message = "Title is required")
    @Size(min = 3, max = 100, message = "Title must be 3-100 characters")
    String title,

    @NotNull(message = "Start time is required")
    @Future(message = "Start time must be in the future")
    LocalDateTime startTime,

    @NotNull(message = "End time is required")
    LocalDateTime endTime,

    @Min(value = 1, message = "Max attendees must be at least 1")
    @Max(value = 10000, message = "Max attendees cannot exceed 10,000")
    Integer maxAttendees
) {
    // Custom validation (cross-field)
    public CreateEventInput {
        if (endTime.isBefore(startTime)) {
            throw new ValidationException("End time must be after start time");
        }
    }
}
```

### 5.2 Validation Error Response

**When validation fails, return errors in payload:**

```java
// Service layer
public CreateEventPayload createEvent(CreateEventInput input) {
    List<UserError> errors = new ArrayList<>();

    // Business rule: check for duplicate title
    if (eventRepository.existsByTitle(input.title())) {
        errors.add(new UserError(
            "Event with this title already exists",
            "title",
            ErrorCode.DUPLICATE_ENTRY
        ));
    }

    if (!errors.isEmpty()) {
        return new CreateEventPayload(null, errors, false);
    }

    // Create event
    Event event = eventRepository.save(new Event(input));
    return new CreateEventPayload(event, List.of(), true);
}
```

