## 7. Schema Organization (RECOMMENDED)

### 7.1 File Structure

```
src/main/resources/graphql/
├── schema.graphqls           # Root schema (Query, Mutation, Subscription)
├── types/
│   ├── user.graphqls        # User type + related types
│   ├── event.graphqls       # Event type + related types
│   ├── invitation.graphqls  # Invitation type + related types
├── inputs/
│   ├── user-inputs.graphqls       # User input types
│   ├── event-inputs.graphqls      # Event input types
├── common/
│   ├── pagination.graphqls  # Pagination types (Connection, PageInfo)
│   ├── errors.graphqls      # Error types (UserError, ErrorCode)
│   ├── scalars.graphqls     # Custom scalars (DateTime, URL, Email)
```

### 7.2 Schema Composition

**Root schema:**
```graphql
# schema.graphqls
schema {
  query: Query
  mutation: Mutation
}

type Query {
  # User queries
  user(id: ID!): User
  users(filter: UserFilter, pagination: PaginationInput): UserConnection!

  # Event queries
  event(id: ID!): Event
  events(filter: EventFilter, pagination: PaginationInput): EventConnection!
}

type Mutation {
  # User mutations
  createUser(input: CreateUserInput!): CreateUserPayload!
  updateUser(id: ID!, input: UpdateUserInput!): UpdateUserPayload!

  # Event mutations
  createEvent(input: CreateEventInput!): CreateEventPayload!
  updateEvent(id: ID!, input: UpdateEventInput!): UpdateEventPayload!
}
```

