## 9. Testing GraphQL APIs (MANDATORY)

### 9.1 Integration Tests

**Test GraphQL queries/mutations with real schema:**

```java
@SpringBootTest
@AutoConfigureGraphQlTester
class EventResolverIT {

    @Autowired
    private GraphQlTester graphQlTester;

    @Test
    void shouldCreateEvent() {
        String mutation = """
            mutation CreateEvent($input: CreateEventInput!) {
                createEvent(input: $input) {
                    success
                    event { id title }
                    errors { message code }
                }
            }
            """;

        graphQlTester.document(mutation)
            .variable("input", Map.of(
                "title", "Birthday Party",
                "startTime", "2025-12-31T18:00:00Z",
                "endTime", "2025-12-31T22:00:00Z"
            ))
            .execute()
            .path("createEvent.success").entity(Boolean.class).isEqualTo(true)
            .path("createEvent.event.title").entity(String.class).isEqualTo("Birthday Party")
            .path("createEvent.errors").entityList(Object.class).hasSize(0);
    }

    @Test
    void shouldReturnValidationError_whenTitleTooShort() {
        String mutation = """
            mutation CreateEvent($input: CreateEventInput!) {
                createEvent(input: $input) {
                    success
                    errors { message field code }
                }
            }
            """;

        graphQlTester.document(mutation)
            .variable("input", Map.of(
                "title", "AB",  // Too short
                "startTime", "2025-12-31T18:00:00Z",
                "endTime", "2025-12-31T22:00:00Z"
            ))
            .execute()
            .path("createEvent.success").entity(Boolean.class).isEqualTo(false)
            .path("createEvent.errors[0].code").entity(String.class).isEqualTo("VALIDATION_ERROR")
            .path("createEvent.errors[0].field").entity(String.class).isEqualTo("title");
    }
}
```

