## 10. Cursor Operating Rules (CRITICAL)

**Cursor MUST:**
- Follow schema-first design (write schema before implementation)
- Use Input objects for all mutations
- Return Payload types from mutations (not entities directly)
- Implement pagination for unbounded lists
- Validate inputs at resolver layer
- Return validation errors in payload `errors` field
- Use `ErrorCode` enum for machine-readable errors

**Cursor MUST NOT:**
- Invent schema patterns not documented here
- Return raw entities from mutations
- Skip pagination for unbounded lists
- Expose stack traces or database errors to clients
- Use generic error messages

**When in doubt → STOP AND ASK.**

---

## 11. Example: Complete Mutation Flow

**Schema:**
```graphql
input CreateEventInput {
  title: String!
  description: String
  startTime: DateTime!
  endTime: DateTime!
  maxAttendees: Int
}

type CreateEventPayload {
  event: Event
  errors: [UserError!]!
  success: Boolean!
}

type Mutation {
  createEvent(input: CreateEventInput!): CreateEventPayload!
}
```

**Resolver:**
```java
@Controller
public class EventResolver {
    private final EventService eventService;

    @MutationMapping
    public CreateEventPayload createEvent(@Valid @Argument CreateEventInput input) {
        return eventService.createEvent(input);
    }
}
```

**Service:**
```java
@Service
public class EventService {
    private final EventRepository eventRepository;

    public CreateEventPayload createEvent(CreateEventInput input) {
        List<UserError> errors = new ArrayList<>();

        // Business validation
        if (input.endTime().isBefore(input.startTime())) {
            errors.add(new UserError(
                "End time must be after start time",
                "endTime",
                ErrorCode.VALIDATION_ERROR
            ));
        }

        if (eventRepository.existsByTitle(input.title())) {
            errors.add(new UserError(
                "Event with this title already exists",
                "title",
                ErrorCode.DUPLICATE_ENTRY
            ));
        }

        if (!errors.isEmpty()) {
            return new CreateEventPayload(null, errors, false);
        }

        // Create event
        Event event = new Event(input.title(), input.description(), input.startTime(), input.endTime());
        event = eventRepository.save(event);

        return new CreateEventPayload(event, List.of(), true);
    }
}
```

