## 12. Domain README Documentation (MANDATORY)

**Each domain MUST have a `README.md` file documenting all changes, use cases, and reasoning.**

### 12.1 Purpose

Domain READMEs serve as:
- **Living documentation** of domain evolution
- **Cross-session context** for future work
- **Institutional knowledge** capturing "why" decisions
- **Change log** with rationale and use cases

### 12.2 Location

**Pattern:**
```
src/main/java/com/hestia/[domain]/README.md
```

**Examples:**
```
src/main/java/com/hestia/user/README.md
src/main/java/com/hestia/event/README.md
src/main/java/com/hestia/invitation/README.md
```

### 12.3 README Template

Every domain README should follow this structure:

```markdown
